  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "No, you generally **cannot apply for internet banking in Andhra Bank (now Union Bank of India)** without visiting the branch for initial registration.  While you can often activate pre-registered internet banking online, **initial registration usually requires verification at the branch.**\n\nHere's why and what your options are:\n\n* **Security:**  Internet banking involves sensitive financial information.  Banks need to verify your identity to protect you from fraud. This verification typically requires physical presence and ID confirmation.\n\n* **KYC Compliance:** Banks are legally obligated to verify the identity of their customers (Know Your Customer or KYC). In-person verification is often the easiest way to ensure KYC compliance for internet banking.\n\n* **Initial Setup:** Often, the initial internet banking setup involves receiving a kit with a PIN/password, or biometric verification, which is done at the branch.\n\n**How to Register for Internet Banking (Usually involves a branch visit):**\n\n1. **Obtain the Application Form:** You can usually download the internet banking application form from the Union Bank of India website (since Andhra Bank has merged).  Look for forms related to \"Internet Banking Registration\" or \"Online Banking Application.\"\n\n2. **Fill Out the Form:** Complete the application form with accurate details.\n\n3. **Submit at the Branch:**  Visit your nearest Union Bank of India (formerly Andhra Bank) branch and submit the filled-out application form along with necessary KYC documents (like Aadhaar, PAN card, etc.).  You'll likely need to show the originals for verification.\n\n4. **Receive Confirmation/Credentials:** The bank will then process your application and provide you with the necessary login credentials (User ID, Password, etc.) or instructions for activating your account. This might involve a kit being given to you.\n\n**Activating Pre-Registered Internet Banking Online (If applicable):**\n\nIf you've already been pre-registered (sometimes done when opening a new account), you *might* be able to activate your account online. Look for an \"Activate Internet Banking\" or \"First Time User\" option on the Union Bank of India's online banking portal. However, this is still relatively rare, and most likely requires a visit to the branch to get pre-registered in the first place.\n\n**Therefore, the most reliable way to get internet banking for your account from the erstwhile Andhra Bank (now Union Bank of India) is to visit your branch to register and submit all the required documents.** Contact your branch beforehand to confirm their specific process and required documentation.\n",
